ng French Canadian community, faith, and culture. It offered French Canadian men a way to remodel themselves, participate in industrial modernity, and still assert cultural authority.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMasculinityzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy19th century. 0aMasculinityzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aMenzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy19th century. 0aMenzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aNationalismzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy19th century. 0aNationalismzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Men's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311141793640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483465040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774834650423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774834650/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-141793-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles